explanation:
To decide whether any code in OS_SocketListen is unreachable you must know the definitions and behaviors that affect its control flow and conditional expressions:

- OS_ObjectIdGetById: Determines whether the initial if (return_code == OS_SUCCESS) branch is taken; also may define token lifetime and side effects. Needed to know when the inner block is reachable.
- OS_ObjectIdRelease: Releases the token at end of the guarded block; its semantics confirm whether the token path is normal/always executed and if any early returns could bypass it.
- OS_object_token_t: Type of token passed to/object returned by OS_ObjectIdGetById and OS_SocketListen_Impl; required to understand aliasing and whether OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET uses it.
- OS_stream_internal_record_t: Structure definition (fields socket_domain, socket_type, stream_state) is required to evaluate the conditional checks on those fields and determine which branches are reachable.
- OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET: Macro/inline used to obtain 'stream' from OS_stream_table and token; its implementation may influence whether stream can be NULL or whether this access is unconditional/guarded (affects reachability of subsequent checks).
- OS_stream_table: The object/table used by OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET; its layout or indexing rules (and whether indexing can fail) affect whether the 'stream' read is always valid.
- OS_SocketListen_Impl: Called inside the final else; its return values determine whether the assignment stream->stream_state |= OS_STREAM_STATE_LISTENING is reached. Needed to know if that statement can be unreachable.
- OS_SocketDomain_INVALID: Value used in the first condition; needed to evaluate reachability of the OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE branch.
- OS_SocketType_STREAM: Value used to test socket type; needed for the same reason as above.
- OS_STREAM_STATE_BOUND: Bitmask tested to decide if socket is bound; required to determine reachability of the OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_STATE branch.
- OS_STREAM_STATE_LISTENING: Bitmask set/checked to decide reachability of the listening-related branch and the bitwise update at the end.
- OS_STREAM_STATE_CONNECTED: Bitmask tested alongside LISTENING to decide reachability of the connected/listening error branch.
- OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE: Error return assigned in one branch; needed to know concrete value only if distinguishing identical constants matters for reachability analysis (e.g., constant propagation, compiler-optimized dead code).
- OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_STATE: Error return assigned in other branches; same reason as above.
- OS_SUCCESS: Value compared against return_code; required to determine which path is taken after OS_ObjectIdGetById and after OS_SocketListen_Impl.
- LOCAL_OBJID_TYPE: Argument to OS_ObjectIdGetById that may affect lookup behavior/validity of the token; needed to reason whether OS_ObjectIdGetById can ever return OS_SUCCESS for this call.
- OS_LOCK_MODE_EXCLUSIVE: Argument to OS_ObjectIdGetById (locking mode) which may affect whether the call succeeds or has side effects that change reachability.

These symbols (types, constants, macro and called-implementation) collectively determine the truth values of the conditionals and the outcomes of the called functions inside OS_SocketListen; thus they are necessary to determine whether any statements or branches in the function are unreachable under the project's definitions.
